name: scljet-sql-insert-cols
description: SclJet SQL column-list INSERT — INSERT INTO t(cols) VALUES(…) maps to declared order, unnamed columns NULL (matches sqlite3)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL column-list INSERT

`INSERT INTO t (c1, c2, …) VALUES (…)` maps the values to the table's declared column order;
columns not named get NULL. After a sequence of column-list inserts the table matches reference
sqlite3 running the same statements (verified out-of-band, integrity_check ok); locked here
across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows, executeMutation](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def apply(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): ByteSlice =
  executeMutation(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) =>
      println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
      db
    case Right(next) => next

def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(id INTEGER, name TEXT, age INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("a"), SqlInteger(20L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db0) =>
    val db1 = apply(db0, "INSERT INTO t (id, name, age) VALUES (2, 'b', 25)")
    val db2 = apply(db1, "INSERT INTO t (name, id) VALUES ('c', 3)")
    val db3 = apply(db2, "INSERT INTO t (id, age) VALUES (4, 40)")
    val db4 = apply(db3, "INSERT INTO t (age, name, id) VALUES (55, 'e', 5)")
    show(db4, "SELECT * FROM t")
    show(db4, "SELECT id, name FROM t WHERE age >= 40 ORDER BY id")
    show(db4, "SELECT COUNT(*), COUNT(name) FROM t")
```
